13-15 Tillary Street, north side, between Fulton and Washington Streets, showing a set of four views of the home of Dr. James Tillary.

W. T. Cutting was the owner in 1919. The home partially seen at the left of the aforementioned house was the property of Kate Duoyea in 1919. Edward Salit appear as the owner from 1925 to 1933.

In this period of time the house which was partially brick and wood appears on the Brooklyn Atlas of 1929 as all brick. E. H. Kenmore was the owner of both of the aforementioned homes in 1933.

In 1936 the homes were condemned by the City of New York and demolished inorder to make a wider approach to the Brooklyn Bridge.

View No. 4 shows a rear view. This house adjoins the Fulton St. B.M.T. elevated structure.

Prior to 1929
Views 1 to 4

Gift of Samuel Landsman
